syAT5sZfLj2QZZVU4kGootqIrxcKs59B2MK63PoaUaKZ6SM3OA\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering subclass behavior**\\n\\nI'm wondering if it's acceptable for a subclass to override `findResource` to return null, avoiding the need for `URLClassLoader`. But I think that native constraints might actually favor overriding `findClass` or `findResource`, even though that means not exercising the full find logic. There's also the concern about dynamic call sites — the user specifically asks about active call sites rather than branches. It's definitely a complex issue to consider!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Implementing resource updates**\\n\\nI need to implement a static nested class for the resource signature that can return a URL without obligatory annotations. This sounds like it could simplify things, especially if I also update the test instantiations accordingly. It makes sense to streamline this process. I'll focus on ensuring everything integrates well within the existing structure, making it easier to manage in the future. Let's work this out to improve efficiency!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_P2LVQrmnt5ghrglQER8jXBAx|fc_05c133babc234475016a3eb4a5104881968c24a3ac93c2e0ef", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot-devtools/4.1.0/src/test/java/org_springframework_boot/spring_boot_devtools/RestartClassLoaderTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "        RestartClassLoader classLoader = new RestartClassLoader(getClass().getClassLoader(), new URL[0]);", "newText": "        RestartClassLoader classLoader = new ParentOnlyRestartClassLoader(getClass().getClassLoader());"}, {"oldText": "        RestartClassLoader classLoader = new RestartClassLoader(parent, new URL[0]);", "newText": "        RestartClassLoader classLoader = new ParentOnlyRestartClassLoader(parent);"}, {"oldText": "        RestartClassLoader classLoader = new RestartClassLoader(\n                new ParentResourceClassLoader(firstParentResource, List.of(firstParentResource, secondParentResource)),\n                new URL[0], updatedFiles);", "newText": "        RestartClassLoader classLoader = new ParentOnlyRestartClassLoader(\n                new ParentResourceClassLoader(firstParentResource, List.of(firstParentResource, secondParentResource)),\n                updatedFiles);"}, {"oldText": "    private static final class ParentResourceClassLoader extends ClassLoader {\n", "newText": "    private static final class ParentOnlyRestartClassLoader extends RestartClassLoader {\n\n        private ParentOnlyRestartClassLoader(ClassLoader parent) {\n            this(parent, new ClassLoaderFiles());\n        }\n\n        private ParentOnlyRestartClassLoader(ClassLoader parent, ClassLoaderFiles updatedFiles) {\n            super(parent, new URL[0], updatedFiles);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Class<?> findClass(String name) throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            throw new ClassNotFoundException(name);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public URL findResource(String name) {\n            return null;\n        }\n\n    }\n\n    private static final class ParentResourceClassLoader extends ClassLoader {\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 857, "output": 2006, "cacheRead": 29184, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 32047, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782494346707, "responseId": "resp_05c133babc234475016a3eb48b2ed081969c4dcfc18e234bb4"}}
